  "text": "When a directory server receives a signed statement for an OR, it checks whether the OR's identity key is recognized. Directory servers do not advertise unrecognized ORs-if they did, an adversary could take over the network by creating many servers [CITATION_1] . Instead, new nodes must be approved by the directory server administrator before they are included. Mechanisms for automated node approval are an area of active research, and are discussed more in Section 9.",
